'''Secrets''' in Kirby's Adventure include hidden areas, bonus games, and optional content.

== Secret Switches ==

Each level has hidden switches that unlock secret areas:
* Switches appear as star-shaped objects
* Some are hidden behind false walls
* Others require specific abilities to reach

== Hidden Rooms ==

=== Warp Stars ===
Special Warp Stars lead to secret areas:
* Look for unusual star placements
* Some require ability combinations
* Lead to bonus items or shortcuts

=== False Walls ===
Many walls can be passed through:
* Try pressing against walls
* Some require specific abilities
* Hidden rooms contain extra lives

== Secret Abilities ==

=== Mix ===
Combine two abilities for special effects (limited situations):
* Certain ability combinations
* Special enemy interactions

=== Ball ===
Turns Kirby into a bouncing ball:
* Hard to control
* High bouncing
* Found in specific locations

=== U.F.O. ===
One of the rarest abilities:
* Extremely powerful
* Can attack in multiple directions
* Lost when entering doors

== Crane Game ==

After completing worlds, the crane game becomes available:
* Win extra lives
* Win items
* Skill-based minigame

== Arena ==

Fight bosses again in the Arena:
* Access after completing game
* Challenge mode
* Test your skills

== 100% Completion ==

=== Requirements ===
* Complete all levels
* Find all switches
* Defeat all bosses
* Complete all bonus games

=== Reward ===
* Sound test mode
* Extra options
* Full ending sequence

== Boss Secrets ==

=== Boss Weaknesses ===
Each boss has optimal abilities:
* Whispy Woods - Most abilities work
* Paint Roller - Avoid painted enemies
* Mr. Shine & Mr. Bright - Time attacks carefully
* Kracko - Stay mobile
* Heavy Mole - Attack from sides
* Meta Knight - Sword required
* King Dedede - Any ability works

=== Bonus Boss ===
* Nightmare is the true final boss
* Appears after defeating Dedede
* Two-phase fight

== Rainbow Resort Secrets ==

The final world contains many hidden areas:
* Most switches hidden here
* Complex level design
* Prepare for final boss

== Easter Eggs ==

=== Nintendo References ===
* Artwork references other Nintendo games
* Music callbacks
* Character cameos in backgrounds

=== Developer Room ===
Some versions have hidden credits or developer acknowledgments.

== Tips ==

'''Abilities:'''
* U.F.O. is overpowered when available
* Sword is consistently good
* Wheel for speedy sections

'''Exploration:'''
* Check all walls
* Try abilities on environment
* Return with different abilities

'''Boss Fights:'''
* Learn patterns
* Keep an ability when entering boss rooms
* Some abilities make bosses trivial

== Extra Lives ==

Extra lives are hidden throughout:
* In secret rooms
* Behind false walls
* In crane games
* From collecting points

